    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 296/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-09T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>307. Have discussed fully with Lamont<note n="10" xml:id="d133fn10">Thomas W.
                        Lamont of J. P. Morgan &amp; Co.</note> the suggestions I took up with
                        you<note n="11" xml:id="d133fn11">Presumably at Washington; Ambassador
                        Herrick left Paris for the United States July 22 and did not return to his
                        post until Oct. 12.</note> as to effective consideration of reparation
                    problem by financial experts. He has communicated with Morgan who will see you
                    to discuss practicable steps.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
